We recommended to the management to do the following: 

1. Consider applying for monthly postpaid plans with features of unlimited calls and texts to all networks which are more cost-effective;
2. Create regulatory policies and/or internal guidelines relating to Communication Expenses which specifies clearly who are eligible and the limitation per eligible employee/official; 
3. Charge communication expenses under its appropriate expense line item instead of erroneously charging it against office supplies and stop recording expenses relating to the former under ‘Office Supplies Expenses’ account instead record them in ‘Telephone Expenses’;  and
4. Ensure that succeeding disbursements relating to Communication Expense are complete with supporting documents.

